      "content": "yeah, \"ephemeral\" is a fancy way of putting it. but it's more than just being temporary. it feels like we're just running on a treadmill for no reason. like, i work, i deal with all this mental noise, i try to \"be someone,\" but it's all just a distraction from the fact that we're literally nothing. if the math says it all ends in nothing, then isn't the struggle just... illogical? it feels like a cruel joke to have all these feelings just to have them erased anyway.",
